FBIS3-13259 "drnes048_l_94009" FBIS-NES-94-048 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Mar 1994 ISRAEL Indictments Filed Against 3 for Supporting Massacre TA1103054794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0500 GMT 11 Mar 94 TA1103054794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Indictments have been filed in the Jerusalem Magistrate's Court against three Israelis who are accused of publicly supporting the Hebron massacre and expressing solidarity with Barukh Goldstein. The three are Shmu'el Ben-Yishay, Amnon Tadmor, and Arye Ben-Yosef. They are charged with violating the antiterrorism act. Shmu'el Ben-Yishay has already been under administrative detention for a week, and the High Court of Justice yesterday discussed a petition against the move.
